.TH "DALMA\-RUN_PYTHON" "" "January 2017" "NYUAD" "Dalma Manual"
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
This page explains how to load our highly cusomized Python environments on Dalma\.
.
.P
There are basically two methods: either to use Python through \fIAnaconda\fR or the user install the modules in its own personalised environment\.
.
.P
This section describes the use of python with \fIAnaconda\fR\. For more info about this, please visit: Python \- Using Anaconda \fIhttps://wikis\.nyu\.edu/display/ADRC/Python+\-+Using+Anaconda\fR
.
.P
To install packages using pip, visit Python \- Using python in Dalma \- Installing Modules \fIhttps://wikis\.nyu\.edu/display/ADRC/Python+\-+Create+and+manage+your+own+Python+environment\fR
.
.P
To install packages using Conda, visit Python \- Create Your Own Environment using Anaconda \fIhttps://wikis\.nyu\.edu/display/ADRC/Python+\-+Create+Your+Own+Environment+using+Anaconda\fR
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
1\.\- Login Dalma\.
.
.P
2\.\- Run this in terminal to load Anaconda module:
.
.P
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
.
.P
\fBmodule load anaconda\fR
.
.P
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
.
.P
3\.\- Run this in terminal to inspect available environment:
.
.P
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
.
.P
\fBconda env list\fR
.
.P
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
.
.P
Example screen output from previous command:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

  [wei@login\-0\-1 ~]$ conda env list
  # conda environments:
  #
  p27\-astro                /share/apps/NYUAD3/anaconda/2\-4\.1\.1/envs/p27\-astro
  p27\-scient               /share/apps/NYUAD3/anaconda/2\-4\.1\.1/envs/p27\-scient
  pyferret                 /share/apps/NYUAD3/anaconda/2\-4\.1\.1/envs/pyferret
  python\-27                /share/apps/NYUAD3/anaconda/2\-4\.1\.1/envs/python\-27
  python\-3                 /share/apps/NYUAD3/anaconda/2\-4\.1\.1/envs/python\-3
  r\-322                    /share/apps/NYUAD3/anaconda/2\-4\.1\.1/envs/r\-322
  r\-essentials             /share/apps/NYUAD3/anaconda/2\-4\.1\.1/envs/r\-essentials
  root                  *  /share/apps/NYUAD3/anaconda/2\-4\.1\.1
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
The symbol "*" means the current loaded environment\. In this case, "root" is loaded\.
.
.P
4\.\- Load specific Python environment\. This example loads the environment p27\-astro, the Python 2\.7 environment for Center of Particle Detection\. Run this in terminal:
.
.P
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
.
.P
\fBsource activate p27\-astro\fR
.
.P
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
.
.P
Example screen output from previous command:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

  [wei@login\-0\-1 ~]$ source activate p27\-astro
  (p27\-astro) [wei@login\-0\-1 ~]$
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
Notice the (p27\-astro) prefix\. It indicates the current loaded environment\.
.
.P
5\.\- \fB(Optional)\fR In case you want to load another Python environment, or you simply don\'t want this Python environment anymore, run this in terminal to unload the environment:
.
.P
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
.
.P
\fBsource deactivate\fR
.
.P
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
.
